  "root_text": {
    "an4.49:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4.49 ",
    "an4.49:0.2": "5. Rohitassavagga ",
    "an4.49:0.3": "Vipallāsasutta ",
    "an4.49:1.1": "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, saññāvipallāsā cittavipallāsā diṭṭhivipallāsā. ",
    "an4.49:1.2": "Katame cattāro? ",
    "an4.49:1.3": "Anicce, bhikkhave, niccanti saññāvipallāso cittavipallāso diṭṭhivipallāso; ",
    "an4.49:1.4": "dukkhe, bhikkhave, sukhanti saññāvipallāso cittavipallāso diṭṭhivipallāso; ",
    "an4.49:1.5": "anattani, bhikkhave, attāti saññāvipallāso cittavipallāso diṭṭhivipallāso; ",
    "an4.49:1.6": "asubhe, bhikkhave, subhanti saññāvipallāso cittavipallāso diṭṭhivipallāso. ",
    "an4.49:1.7": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro saññāvipallāsā cittavipallāsā diṭṭhivipallāsā. ",
    "an4.49:2.1": "Cattārome, bhikkhave, nasaññāvipallāsā nacittavipallāsā nadiṭṭhivipallāsā. ",
    "an4.49:2.2": "Katame cattāro? ",
    "an4.49:2.3": "Anicce, bhikkhave, aniccanti nasaññāvipallāso nacittavipallāso nadiṭṭhivipallāso; ",
    "an4.49:2.4": "dukkhe, bhikkhave, dukkhanti nasaññāvipallāso nacittavipallāso nadiṭṭhivipallāso; ",
    "an4.49:2.5": "anattani, bhikkhave, anattāti nasaññāvipallāso nacittavipallāso nadiṭṭhivipallāso; ",
    "an4.49:2.6": "asubhe, bhikkhave, asubhanti nasaññāvipallāso nacittavipallāso nadiṭṭhivipallāso. ",
    "an4.49:2.7": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro nasaññāvipallāsā nacittavipallāsā nadiṭṭhivipallāsāti. ",
    "an4.49:3.1": "Anicce niccasaññino, ",
    "an4.49:3.2": "dukkhe ca sukhasaññino; ",
    "an4.49:3.3": "Anattani ca attāti, ",
    "an4.49:3.4": "asubhe subhasaññino; ",
    "an4.49:3.5": "Micchādiṭṭhihatā sattā, ",
    "an4.49:3.6": "khittacittā visaññino. ",
    "an4.49:4.1": "Te yogayuttā mārassa, ",
    "an4.49:4.2": "ayogakkhemino janā; ",
    "an4.49:4.3": "Sattā gacchanti saṁsāraṁ, ",
    "an4.49:4.4": "jātimaraṇagāmino. ",
    "an4.49:5.1": "Yadā ca buddhā lokasmiṁ, ",
    "an4.49:5.2": "Uppajjanti pabhaṅkarā; ",
    "an4.49:5.3": "Te imaṁ dhammaṁ pakāsenti, ",
    "an4.49:5.4": "Dukkhūpasamagāminaṁ. ",
    "an4.49:6.1": "Tesaṁ sutvāna sappaññā, ",
    "an4.49:6.2": "sacittaṁ paccaladdhā te; ",
    "an4.49:6.3": "Aniccaṁ aniccato dakkhuṁ, ",
    "an4.49:6.4": "dukkhamaddakkhu dukkhato. ",
    "an4.49:7.1": "Anattani anattāti, ",
    "an4.49:7.2": "asubhaṁ asubhataddasuṁ; ",
    "an4.49:7.3": "Sammādiṭṭhisamādānā, ",
    "an4.49:7.4": "sabbaṁ dukkhaṁ upaccagun”ti. ",
    "an4.49:7.5": "Navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an4.49:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 4.49 ",
    "an4.49:0.2": "5. With Rohitassa ",
    "an4.49:0.3": "Perversions ",
    "an4.49:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these four perversions of perception, thought, and view. ",
    "an4.49:1.2": "What four? ",
    "an4.49:1.3": "Taking impermanence as permanence. ",
    "an4.49:1.4": "Taking suffering as happiness. ",
    "an4.49:1.5": "Taking not-self as self. ",
    "an4.49:1.6": "Taking ugliness as beauty. ",
    "an4.49:1.7": "These are the four perversions of perception, thought, and view. ",
    "an4.49:2.1": "There are these four corrections of perception, thought, and view. ",
    "an4.49:2.2": "What four? ",
    "an4.49:2.3": "Taking impermanence as impermanence. ",
    "an4.49:2.4": "Taking suffering as suffering. ",
    "an4.49:2.5": "Taking not-self as not-self. ",
    "an4.49:2.6": "Taking ugliness as ugliness. ",
    "an4.49:2.7": "These are the four corrections of perception, thought, and view. ",
    "an4.49:3.1": "Perceiving impermanence as permanence, ",
    "an4.49:3.2": "suffering as happiness, ",
    "an4.49:3.3": "not-self as self, ",
    "an4.49:3.4": "and ugliness as beauty—",
    "an4.49:3.5": "sentient beings are ruined by wrong view, ",
    "an4.49:3.6": "deranged, out of their minds. ",
    "an4.49:4.1": "Yoked by Māra’s yoke, these people ",
    "an4.49:4.2": "find no sanctuary from the yoke. ",
    "an4.49:4.3": "Sentient beings continue to transmigrate, ",
    "an4.49:4.4": "with ongoing birth and death. ",
    "an4.49:5.1": "But when the Buddhas arise ",
    "an4.49:5.2": "in the world, those beacons ",
    "an4.49:5.3": "reveal this teaching, ",
    "an4.49:5.4": "that leads to the stilling of suffering. ",
    "an4.49:6.1": "When a wise person hears them, ",
    "an4.49:6.2": "they get their mind back. ",
    "an4.49:6.3": "Seeing impermanence as impermanence, ",
    "an4.49:6.4": "suffering as suffering, ",
    "an4.49:7.1": "not-self as not-self, ",
    "an4.49:7.2": "and ugliness as ugliness—",
    "an4.49:7.3": "taking up right view, ",
    "an4.49:7.4": "they’ve risen above all suffering.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an4.49:5.3": "imaṁ dhammaṁ → temaṁ dhammaṁ (bj, sya-all, km) "
  },
